  </div>

  <h2 class="font-headline font-semibold text-2xl text-text-primary pt-4">Database Properties and Comments</h2>
  <p>
    Notion databases are where teams track tasks, bugs, clients, and content calendars. Each database entry has properties — text fields, notes sections, and comment threads. QuickSay works in all of these. Click into a database property, dictate, and the cleaned text fills the field. Leave voice-dictated comments on database entries during review sessions. Update status notes without reaching for the keyboard.
  </p>

  <h2 class="font-headline font-semibold text-2xl text-text-primary pt-4">Meeting Notes Directly into Notion</h2>
  <p>
    Many teams run meetings with a Notion page open for notes. The challenge is capturing key points while participating in the conversation. Typing during a meeting is slow and distracting. With QuickSay, you can hold your keyboard shortcut during a pause, dictate a summary of what was just discussed, and release. The cleaned note appears in your Notion meeting template without disrupting the meeting flow.
  </p>

  <h2 class="font-headline font-semibold text-2xl text-text-primary pt-4">Desktop App and Browser</h2>
  <p>
    QuickSay works identically whether you use the Notion desktop app for Windows or access Notion through a browser tab. There is no difference in behavior because QuickSay does not interact with Notion's software — it types into the active text field, regardless of what application contains it. Switch between the desktop app and the web version freely; your voice typing workflow stays the same.
  </p>

  <h2 class="font-headline font-semibold text-2xl text-text-primary pt-4">Privacy for Your Workspace</h2>
  <p>
    Notion workspaces often contain sensitive company information — strategy docs, financial data, HR notes, customer details. QuickSay captures zero screen content and collects zero telemetry. Your audio is sent to the cloud for transcription, and nothing else leaves your machine. There is no browser extension reading your Notion pages and no third-party service with access to your workspace data.
  </p>
